Piers Morgan is a fucking joke... used to like him for his views on gun control but ever since then I’ve learned more about him, who he is. And now I know he’s a joke. Being a man means different to a lot of men, but one thing it should always mean is respect and learning. No one is saying you can’t like football or boxing. That you can’t be a tough man who’s manly interests are as traditionally manly as it gets. All anyone has ever said is it’s okay to learn, that we should learn. That rape culture and the constant disrespect towards our women peers is not okay, and that takes nothing away from our masculinity. And if you feel it does, then you don’t have masculinity you have a victim complex and an authority complex toxic to the community around you, to the young boys around you. Teach your boys not only to respect ‘no’ and what ‘yes’ is and isn’t, also teach them it’s okay to feel upset, to get angry, to have emotions, and teach them an appropriate and healthy way to deal with those emotions. Teach them respect for each other and everyone around them. Don’t tell them ‘boys will just be boys’, teach them accountability. Being a real man is knowing this.
